>>> key definitions

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
phoneme     the smallest sound categories that distinguish meanings (words)
                - e.g. p, b, d, and t in the English words pad, pat, bad, and bat.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
morpheme    the smallest units of meaning
                - e.g. words (you, cat) and affixes (un-, -ous) in English
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
semantics   the meaning of whole words
                - like words, phrases, signs, and symbols
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
syntax      the organization of words within a sentence
                - like grammar
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
pragmatics  the appropriate use of language in context
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

